{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"porous-boast-spray","description":"The snapshot janitor never garbage-collects the new pinned ticket-store cache entries (`<store>/tickets-<sha>/`) introduced in PR #67, so they accumulate unboundedly as the `tickets` branch changes — a local-disk leak in the gate snapshot cache. They are also absent from the janitor's byte-total accounting.\n\n## Reproduction Steps\n1. Run the plan-review / completion gates repeatedly while the `tickets` branch HEAD changes between runs (normal: every ticket write advances it).\n2. Each distinct tickets SHA materializes a fresh `<store>/tickets-<sha>/.tickets-tracker/` copy of the whole ticket store.\n3. Inspect the snapshot store (`REBAR_GATE_TMPDIR` / `store_root()`): the `tickets-<sha>` dirs accumulate and are never evicted.\n\n## Expected vs Actual\n- Expected: the janitor evicts stale `tickets-<sha>` entries by the same grace/LRU/size policy it applies to code-snapshot `<sha>` entries, and counts them in the byte total.\n- Actual: `src/rebar/_snapshot/janitor.py:_is_entry` treats an entry as `all(c in \"0123456789abcdef\" for c in name)` — the `tickets-` prefix is non-hex, so `_is_entry(\"tickets-<sha>\")` is False. `_entries()` therefore excludes them: they are never evicted (leak) and never counted (under-reported cache size).\n\n## Root Cause\n`_is_entry` (janitor.py) recognizes only all-hex directory names; PR #67's `tickets-<sha>` entries don't match.\n\n## Fix direction\nExtend `_is_entry` to also recognize `tickets-<40hex>` (e.g. accept names matching `^(tickets-)?[0-9a-f]{40}$`), so `_entries()` includes them for eviction + accounting. Verify `_evict`/`_remove_sidecars` behave for a `tickets-`-named entry (no caveats sidecar — the unlink is try/except, harmless). Add a janitor test that a stale `tickets-<sha>` entry is evicted past the grace window.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `_is_entry` returns True for a `tickets-<40hex>` dir; `_entries()` includes it.\n- [ ] The janitor evicts a stale `tickets-<sha>` entry (past grace) and counts it in the byte total.\n- [ ] A regression test covers eviction + accounting of a `tickets-<sha>` entry.\n- [ ] Code-snapshot `<sha>` entry handling is unchanged.\n- [ ] Fix lands via PR to main.","id":"85b4-9850-a474-4bae","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":["audit-2026-06-27","plan-review-gate","bug","regression"],"ticket_type":"bug","title":"snapshot janitor leaks pinned ticket-store entries (tickets-<sha> not GC'd)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782613529310626001,"uuid":"db856ea5-d65e-42f2-bce6-6e410f354530"}